Despite the historical usage of `setUp` for object creation, I usually recommend using helpers to get/create interesting values used by tests. The reason is that everything that is attached to `self` in `setUp`, is "alive" for the whole test suite run (not the test case, but the whooooole test suite run). So I would suggest:

```suggestion


    @property
    def modifier_key(self):
        return Keys.COMMAND if sys.platform == "darwin" else Keys.CONTROL
```
